    • onActionDeleteProducts

      void onActionDeleteProducts(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Deletes selected product. Method is only run when a product is selected, and the selected product's 'associatedPartsList' is empty. Otherwise, a popup alerts the user to select a product to delete or to delete associated products first.
      Parameters:
      event - -> 'onActionDeleteProduct' button pressed
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - -> if no product is selected

    • onActionSearchParts

      void onActionSearchParts(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Searches 'mainPartTblView' for either matching ID or Name (partial or full.) Method filters displayed list by input. If there is no matching part, method displays information alert stating no matching parts could be found. If search bar is empty, table view displays full list of parts.
      Parameters:
      event - -> 'onActionSearchPart' button pressed

    • onActionSearchProducts

If there is no matching product, method displays information alert stating no matching parts could be found. If search bar is empty, table view displays full list of products.

      event - -> 'onActionSearchProduct' button pressed
